<inglise> Regulation (EEC) No 801/71 of the Commission of 19 April 1971 authorising Member States to take measures derogating, in respect of exports of fresh cut flowers to third countries, from certain requirements of the quality standards </inglise>
<eesti> KOMISJONI M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (EM&Uuml;) nr 801/71, millega lubatakse liikmesriikidel v&otilde;tta meetmeid, mis kehtestavad erandeid teatavatest kvaliteedistandardite n&otilde;uetest v&auml;rskete l&otilde;ikelillede v&auml;ljaveol kolmandatesse riikidesse 19. aprill 1971 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COMMISSION OF THE EUROPEAN COMMUNITIES, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA &Uuml;HENDUSTE KOMISJON, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Economic Community; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Majandus&uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 234/68 1 of 27 February 1968, on the establishment of a common organisation of the market in live trees and other plants, bulbs, roots and the like, cut flowers and ornamental foliage; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 27. veebruari 1968. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 234/68 elustaimede ja lillekasvatustoodete turu &uuml;hise korralduse sisseseadmise kohta, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 316/68 2 of 12 March 1968 fixing quality standards for fresh cut flowers and ornamental foliage, and in particular Article 2 (2) thereof; </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse n&otilde;ukogu 12. m&auml;rtsi 1968. aasta m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 316/68, millega m&auml;&auml;ratakse kindlaks v&auml;rskete l&otilde;ikelillede ja l&otilde;ikerohelise kvaliteedistandardid, eriti selle artikli 2 l&otilde;iget 2, </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas under Article 2 (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 316/68 Member States may be authorised to take measures derogating from certain requirements of the quality standards in order to allow exporters to meet the trade requirements of certain third countries; </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: vastavalt m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 316/68 artikli 2 l&otilde;ikele 2 v&otilde;ib lubada liikmesriikidel v&otilde;tta meetmeid, mis kehtestavad erandeid teatavatest kvaliteedistandardite n&otilde;uetest, et v&otilde;imaldada v&auml;ljavedajatel j&auml;rgida teatavate kolmandate riikide kaubandusn&otilde;udeid; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the provisions of the quality standards relating to the packaging and presentation of cut flowers do not permit the trade requirements of certain third countries to be met in all cases; whereas these trade requirements are of a stable and permanent nature; whereas, therefore, Member States should be authorised to meet them sine die; </inglise>
<eesti> l&otilde;ikelillede pakkimise ja esitlemise kvaliteedistandardeid reguleerivad s&auml;tted ei luba k&otilde;ikidel juhtudel j&auml;rgida teatavate kolmandate riikide kaubandusn&otilde;udeid; need kaubandusn&otilde;uded on muutumatud ja p&uuml;sivad; seep&auml;rast tuleks lubada liikmesriikidel j&auml;rgida neid n&otilde;udeid t&auml;htajatult; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the Opinion of the Management Committee for Live Plants; </inglise>
<eesti> k&auml;esolevas m&auml;&auml;ruses s&auml;testatud meetmed on koosk&otilde;las elustaimede korralduskomitee arvamusega, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 1 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States are authorised, in respect of exports of cut flowers to the United States of America and Canada, to take measures derogating from the provisions of Section VI (A) of Annex I to Regulation (EEC) No 316/68. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriikidel lubatakse v&otilde;tta m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 316/68 I lisa VI jao A alajao s&auml;tetest erandeid kehtestavaid meetmeid l&otilde;ikelillede v&auml;ljaveol Ameerika &Uuml;hendriikidesse ja Kanadasse. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall enter into force on the third day following its publication in the Official Journal of the European Communities. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus j&otilde;ustub kolmandal p&auml;eval p&auml;rast selle avaldamist Euroopa &Uuml;henduste Teatajas. </eesti>
<inglise> This Regulation shall be binding in its entirety and directly applicable in all Member States. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esolev m&auml;&auml;rus on tervikuna siduv ja vahetult kohaldatav k&otilde;ikides liikmesriikides. </eesti>
<inglise> Done at Brussels, 19 April 1971. </inglise>
